<!--867-->Enduring Evil X3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The most important thing in a solo Frodo deck is twilight denial, I do that with Reluctant Adventurer and the Hobbit Farmer + Green Hill Country combo. I probably wont fight much before site 6 because of the stealth events, so I have enough time to play my possessions and allies before that. Of course, this deck is weak against certain types of shadows, like moria archers, sauron UTWE + archers, DDotR sauron and fierce nazguls.<br />
<br />
My shadow adds burdens and kills. With DDotR, Thin and Stretched, twilight WK and Wraith-World I will probably soon have enough burdens to kill off the opponents companions with toldea + sword, enquea and enduring evil. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
